==============================
These are the Main Filters:

ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_mem*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_proc*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_mount*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_dis*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_kernel*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_default_ipv4*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_hostname*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_architecture*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_interfaces*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_dns*'


==============================
ğŸ§  COMMONLY USED FACTS
==============================

ğŸ”¸ SYSTEM
- OS Name:           {{ ansible_facts['distribution'] }}
- OS Version:        {{ ansible_facts['distribution_version'] }}
- Architecture:      {{ ansible_facts['architecture'] }}
- Kernel:            {{ ansible_facts['kernel'] }}
- Hostname:          {{ ansible_facts['hostname'] }}
- FQDN:              {{ ansible_facts['fqdn'] }}

ğŸ”¸ NETWORK
- Default IPv4:      {{ ansible_facts['default_ipv4']['address'] }}
- Interface Names:   {{ ansible_facts['interfaces'] }}
- MAC Address:       {{ ansible_facts['ansible_default_ipv4']['macaddress'] }}
- DNS Servers:       {{ ansible_facts['dns']['nameservers'] }}

ğŸ”¸ CPU
- CPU Cores:         {{ ansible_facts['processor_cores'] }}
- CPU Threads:       {{ ansible_facts['processor_threads_per_core'] }}
- Processor Count:   {{ ansible_facts['processor_count'] }}
- CPUs:              {{ ansible_facts['processor'] }}

ğŸ”¸ MEMORY
- Total RAM (MB):    {{ ansible_facts['memory_mb']['real']['total'] }}
- Free RAM (MB):     {{ ansible_facts['memory_mb']['real']['free'] }}
- Swap Total (MB):   {{ ansible_facts['memory_mb']['swap']['total'] }}

ğŸ”¸ STORAGE (DISKS)
- Mounts Info:       {{ ansible_facts['mounts'] }}
  For example:
    Total: {{ ansible_facts['mounts'][0]['size_total'] | int // 1024**3 }} GB
    Used:  {{ ansible_facts['mounts'][0]['size_used'] | int // 1024**3 }} GB
    Device: {{ ansible_facts['mounts'][0]['device'] }}

==============================
ğŸ“¦ EXPORTING SELECT FACTS
==============================

Dump selected info to file:
  - name: Save system info to file
    copy:
      content: |
        OS: {{ ansible_facts['distribution'] }} {{ ansible_facts['distribution_version'] }}
        CPU Cores: {{ ansible_facts['processor_cores'] }}
        Memory: {{ ansible_facts['memory_mb']['real']['total'] }} MB
        Storage: {{ ansible_facts['mounts'][0]['size_total'] | int // 1024**3 }} GB
      dest: /tmp/system_report.txt

==============================
âš™ï¸ JINJA2 EXAMPLES
==============================

- Default value:       {{ var | default('N/A') }}
- Convert bytes to GB: {{ size_bytes | int // 1024**3 }} GB
- Get list item:       {{ mylist[0] }}
- Conditional:         {% if ansible_facts['processor_cores'] > 4 %} Powerful {% endif %}

==============================
ğŸ§ª FILTERING FACTS
==============================

Use setup module with filters:
  - name: Only gather network facts
    ansible.builtin.setup:
      filter: "ansible_default_ipv4"

  - name: Only gather memory facts
    ansible.builtin.setup:
      filter: "memory_mb"

==============================
ğŸ“ NOTES
==============================

- All memory values are in MB.
- Disk sizes are in **bytes**; convert to GB with:  size | int // 1024**3
- Always use `| default('value')` for safer templates.

